  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb3 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd: \u0b90.\u0ba8\u0bbe.",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Protests must be handled calmly: UN",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The United Nations Commission on Human Rights has stated that it requests Sri Lankan authorities to allow the demonstration to be carried out in Colombo today to proceed in a democratic manner, to handle the protests calmly, and to confirm all necessary efforts to prevent violence.",
        "At the same time, the Human Rights Commission has asked the organizers and supporters of the protests to peacefully participate in the protests and to carry out the protests in a manner that does not disrupt essential medical or humanitarian services.",
        "Human rights activists and journalists have the right to monitor and report on demonstrations. So they have to be protected in their implementation and requested the authorities to give clear instructions to the security forces that they should not be prohibited in any way.",
        "While we recognize the challenges faced by the police and military forces, the government should issue strict instructions to the police and armed forces to avoid violence and exercise extreme restraint in dealing with civilians, including incidents of self-inflicted attacks.",
        "As a general rule, the military should not be used when the police should be used. In exceptional circumstances, when the military carries out law enforcement activities, they must adhere to international norms and standards, fully obey civilian authorities and be accountable under civil law.",
        "Sri Lankans are already suffering massively and continue to live in a state of uncertainty as to how to meet their basic needs, including the rights to food, health and education. The Human Rights Commission said that they have the right to protest peacefully for a better life, economic and social grievances and should be accommodated."
      ],
